The paper discusses a machine learning problem related to class imbalance and proposes a novel cost-sensitive SVM method. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper deals with optimization of penalty parameter C, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. The paper also mentions similarity matrix and cluster probability density function, which are commonly used in Data Mining (cs.DM) and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-categories. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DM, and cs.NE.
